GeneDx is a patient-centric health information company that delivers personalized and actionable health insights that inform diagnosis, guide treatment and improve drug discovery. The company is transforming healthcare through its industry-leading exome and genome testing and interpretation, fueled by one of the world's largest, rare disease data sets. GeneDx is uniquely positioned to accelerate the use of genomic and large-scale clinical information to enable precision medicine as the standard of care.
 SUMMARY
The Lead Clinical Data Analyst will play a crucial role in supporting the Medical Affairs team by compiling and analyzing clinical data, generating insights, and contributing to the development of evidence-based strategies. This role will work cross-functionally with both internal stakeholders across the organization and external collaborators to generate data insights for conference presentations, scientific publications and commercial messaging. This role requires a deep understanding of clinical data, strong analytical skills, and the ability to communicate complex findings effectively. This individual will be a quick learner who thrives in a high growth environment and is passionate about shortening the diagnostic odyssey for patients through data.
 Essential Duties and Responsibilities:

Conduct comprehensive data analyses to support scientific research, conference presentations, and manuscript preparation.
Work closely with cross-functional teams, including medical writers, clinical program managers, clinicians, and researchers, to support ongoing projects and initiatives.
Generate detailed reports and visualizations to communicate complex findings in a clear and concise manner to internal stakeholders, including healthcare providers, researchers, and executives.
Co-develop the data analysis strategy for clinical research studies and commercial messaging, including data collection, analysis, and interpretation of results.
Develop and maintain data pipelines and workflows to ensure data integrity and reproducibility.
Ensure the accuracy, integrity, and security of clinical data by implementing best practices in data management and quality control and ensure analyses comply with relevant regulatory guidelines and standards.
Develop and maintain data governance policies and procedures to ensure data quality, consistency, and security across the organization.
Stay current with the latest advancements in genetic testing and data science methodologies.
Utilize advanced statistical and computational methods to analyze genetic and clinical data.

Qualifications:

PhD in Data Science, Bioinformatics, Biostatistics, Genetics, or a related field.
Minimum of 5 years of experience in clinical data analysis, preferably in the genetic testing or healthcare industry.
Proficiency in statistical software and programming languages such as R, Python, and SQL.
Strong understanding of genetic data and clinical research methodologies.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to interpret complex data sets.
High level of accuracy and attention to detail in data analysis and reporting.
Ability to work effectively in a collaborative, team-oriented environment.
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to present complex data to diverse audiences.
Proven track record of contributing to scientific publications and conference presentations.
Experience with data visualization tools and techniques.
Knowledge of data privacy and security best practices.

Preferred:

Familiarity with regulatory requirements and standards in genetic testing and clinical research.
Experience in developing and implementing data governance policies and procedures.
Experience using cloud-based data warehouse platforms such as Snowflake or equivalent
Experience with machine learning and artificial intelligence applications in healthcare.


~
 Science - Minded, Patient - Focused.
At GeneDx, we create, follow, and are informed by cutting-edge science. With over 20 years of expertise in diagnosing rare disorders and diseases, and pioneering work in the identification of new disease-causing genes, our commitment to genetic disease detection, discovery, and diagnosis is based on sound science and is focused on enhancing patient care.
 Experts in what matters most.
With hundreds of genetic counselors, MD/PhD scientists, and clinical and molecular genomics specialists on staff, we are the industry's genetic testing experts and proud of it. We share the same goal as healthcare providers, patients, and families: to provide clear, accurate, and meaningful answers we all can trust.
 SEQUENCING HAS THE POWER TO SOLVE DIAGNOSTIC CHALLENGES. 
From sequencing to reporting and beyond, our technical and clinical experts are providing guidance every step of the way:
 TECHNICAL EXPERTISE

High-quality testing: Our laboratory is CLIA certified and CAP accredited and most of our tests are also New York State approved.
Advanced detection: By interrogating genes for complex variants, we can identify the underlying causes of conditions that may otherwise be missed.

CLINICAL EXPERTISE

Thorough analysis: We classify variants according to our custom adaptation of the most recent guidelines. We then leverage our rich internal database for additional interpretation evidence.
Customized care: Our experts review all test results and write reports in a clear, concise, and personalized way. We also include information for research studies in specific clinical situations.
Impactful discovery: Our researchers continue working to find answers even after testing is complete. Through both internal research efforts and global collaborations, we have identified and published hundreds of new disease-gene relationships and developed novel tools for genomic data analysis. These efforts ultimately deliver more diagnostic findings to individuals.

Employee Discounts
Voluntary benefits

 The Opportunity

The Data Analyst II, within the Mass General Brigham Enterprise Analytics (EA) Department, is responsible for identifying, querying, analyzing, and visualizing data through reports and presentations, a variety of data to support operations, quality and performance measurement initiatives throughout Mass General Brigham, including its acute and specialty hospitals around greater Boston. The Data Analyst II will be responsible for providing analytics insights to leadership at various levels within the organization. The position requires close collaboration and dialogue with clinical personnel, various analytic groups, and hospital and system leadership.

The Enterprise Analytics Department supports data and reporting across most domains of the hospital operations and could include areas such as patient satisfaction, patient safety, clinical outcomes, asset utilization, and more. The successful Data Analyst II will create lasting relationships with hospital leadership by becoming highly proficient in the data within his or her designated areas of expertise. Regular responsibilities include gathering requirements, performing qualitative and quantitative analyses, finding and querying complex data, and sharing data and results in a digestible, visually appealing, way.

In addition, the Data Analyst II will share best practice methodologies with other analysts and train end-users on various tools as needed, growing the team’s wealth of knowledge and documentation. The team mainly relies on Microsoft SQL Server, Tableau, the Microsoft Office suite, and is partnering with the MGB Digital data platform teams on a journey to build a new data platform with Microsoft Azure Cloud and Snowflake, and leverages other tools and technologies on an as needed basis.

 Principal Duties and Responsibilities

1. Elicits data and reporting requirements from hospital leadership, clinicians, and other staff, using interviews, document analysis, requirements workshops, site visits, use cases, scenarios, data analysis, task, and workflow analysis.
2. Queries and analyzes data from hospital systems such as our electronic medical record system (Epic), enterprise data warehouse (EDW), external websites, and more, to glean meaningful insights and produce actionable reports for internal customers.
3. Presents data and analyses to key stakeholder groups and hospital leadership, including creating materials for and giving presentations as needed.
4. Works with EA and Digital staff in design, maintenance, and distribution of reports while also overseeing ad hoc data analyses and new report development as needed.
5. Works with EA and Digital staff to continually improve our analytical capabilities with SQL, Tableau, and other analytic platforms, which includes but not limited to dashboard and report development, QA of existing reports, and documentation of system functionality.
6. Performs comprehensive quality assurance, ensuring that data and reports meet end user specifications and are accurate and reliable.
7. Works with new and existing EA analysts to share knowledge in methods of data analysis, summarization, and presentation. Trains end-users on key analytic and reporting systems and databases.
8. Partner with MGB Digital teams to leverage existing tools, methods, and processes in order to deliver timely information to operations stakeholders across MGB, including leveraging Microsoft Azure, Snowflake, and Informatica cloud tools.
9. Effectively recognizes when additional help or guidance is needed and seeks it out proactively.
10. Represents EA on internal and external committees or task forces as needed.
11. Performs all other related duties as required.



 Qualifications

1. Bachelor’s degree in management, information systems, statistics, or equivalent experience.
2. At least 3-5 years of experience, preferably in a related analytics position.
3. Healthcare knowledge, particularly as it pertains to electronic medical record data, is preferred but not required.
4. Working knowledge of relational databases, SQL, data visualization, and Business Intelligence tools such as Tableau and proficiency in at least one of these areas.
5. Knowledge and application of statistical analyses including variance analysis and statistical significance preferred.
6. Developing knowledge and application of workflows and data structures of underlying MGB systems, especially Epic, preferred.
7. Experience with Epic Clarity, Caboodle, and/or Cogito a plus
8. Project management skills and/or experience a plus.
9. Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, including Word, Excel and PowerPoint.

 Skills and Abilities

1. Strong ability to work and communicate effectively with staff at various levels within the organization.
2. Experience with querying, manipulating, cleansing, and statistically analyzing large data sets using tools such as SQL Server Management Studio.
3. Proficiency with Excel, manipulating large data sets and synthesizing into digestible information, including polished visualizations.
4. Experience presenting data through the building of dashboards and reports using business intelligence tools such as Tableau (preferred). With direction from more senior teammates, create data visualizations that are suitable for presentation to senior leaders.
5. Ability to clearly communicate complex and sensitive data to hospital leaders as well as peers.
6. Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to tailor message to individuals and audiences throughout the institution.
7. Strong organizational skills, with the ability to focus detailed concentrated effort on multiple projects and take direction regarding appropriate prioritization.
8. Possesses initiative and ability to work independently while thriving in a setting requiring collaboration and teamwork for maximal efficiency and effectiveness.
9. Attention to detail that ensures follow through on all initiatives implemented, and all projects undertaken.
10. Ability to effectively respond to time sensitive issues and meet deadlines.


 EEO Statement

 Mass General Brigham is an Equal Opportunity Employer. By embracing diverse skills, perspectives, and ideas, we choose to lead. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religious creed, national origin, sex, age, gender identity, disability, sexual orientation, military service, genetic information, and/or other status protected under the law. We will ensure that all individuals with a disability are provided a reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, perform essential job functions, and receive other benefits and privileges of employment.

UNITED WAY OF HANCOCK COUNTY RESEARCH/DATA ANALYST – VULNERABLE CHILDREN’S INITIATIVE – AmeriCorps VISTA REPORTS TO CEO LOCATION In person STATUS Variable options

  PURPOSE The United Way of Hancock County is seeking a highly motivated and detail-oriented individual to join our team as a Research and Data Analyst that will assist with grant research and program development. POSITION SUMMARY The candidate will play a key role in advancing UWHC’s Vulnerable Children’s Initiative (VCI) by helping to identify opportunities, interpret and use data to assist with crafting compelling grant proposals, and support community solutions and the efforts of the Community Impact Manager. UWHC’s VCI works to ensure every child in Hancock County has access to a supportive environment conducive to their well-being and educational success. Because this is a new effort at UWHC the best candidate will be a self-starter with a proven ability to manage a variety of data and software platforms and to help develop, systematically organize, monitor and track program development. Creativity, analysis, results and details will be key components to the role.AM Program Development (30%) 

Collaborate with the Community Impact Manager to identify external funding opportunities



  aligned with the VCI initiative by leveraging community reporting and data 

Assist in the development of comprehensive and compelling grant proposals, integrating



  data analytic insights to enhance proposal content 

Conduct research and utilize data analysis to strengthen grant applications and provide



  evidence-based support 

Assist with the implementation of systems to protect vulnerable children and strengthen



  families. 

Collaborative efforts between local nonprofits, government agencies, and community


leaders to address the needs of vulnerable children.

  Research Support (50%) 

Offer guidance on researching and identifying potential funding opportunities, emphasizing



  the use of data reports to learn about the needs of the community and UWHC initiatives 

Provide research assistance in grant-related projects, utilizing data analytics tools and



  techniques 

Assist with data collection, analysis, and interpretation efforts as needed for proposals,



  ensuring a data-driven approach to grant writing 

Contribute to the preparation of research reports and presentations, incorporating data


findings to enhance credibility of grant proposals

  Administrative Support(20%) 

Collaborate with the Community Impact Manager to identify optimal grant opportunities


utilizing data-driven insights for strategic decision-making



Organize and manage database and spreadsheet records of grant applications, submissions, approvals, and outcomes





Collaborate with the UWHC team to gain insights into the inner workings of the non-profit industry



  EDUCATION AND WORK EXPERIENCE 

Strong work ethic with the ability to fit in with the UWHC service based culture
Bachelor’s degree with a focus on data analytics, research, or a related field; undergraduate



  students with relevant experience considered 

Proven interest in improving people’s lives either through volunteerism or work-related



  projects 

Understand the meaning behind data and its potential applications to grant submissions
Research techniques
Process development of a new opportunity – not maintaining what’s been created PERSONAL SKILLS
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Proven research and analytical skills, especially in the context of data analytics
Detail-oriented and highly organized
Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team
Proven ability to adapt to technology and implement tech solutions
Ability to learn new software platforms to represent data, progress dashboards, and our



  program development 

Cross functional team – culture and a whatever it takes attitude are valued


Availability 10-40 hours in person per week, with a flexible schedule to accommodate meetings and deadlines related to UWHC initiatives
How to Apply Submit a resume and cover letter to Kelley McClurkin at Kelley.mcclurkin@uwhancock.org United Way of Hancock County is an equal opportunity employer. We encourage applications from individuals of all backgrounds and experiences.mailto:Kelley.mcclurkin@uwhancock.org

The Ira A. Fulton Schools of Engineering (FSE) at Arizona State University is seeking a Business Analyst with expertise in SQL, data analytics, product management, and relationship management. Under the direction of the Director of Data Analytics and Business Intelligence, the Business Analyst will be the bridge between the business/end-users and the technical resources on the data team. The Business Analyst will help translate business and stakeholder needs and requirements into technical details. They will be a Subject Matter Expert in various data domains by conducting deep dive research. The role will also contribute to the team by processing data pull requests, developing dashboards and reports, identifying team areas of opportunities, and managing projects through the internal backlog.

Conduct requirements gathering meetings with stakeholders and requestors to determine project requirements, logic, and parameters

 Job Description MillerKnoll is actively growing a new B2B portal for select customers to purchase pre-selected products more easily. The product data supporting this growing business is managed in a PIM (Product Information Management) system. For this we are seeking to hire a new Product Data Analyst to join a small team dedicated to supporting this growing segment of our business. The role includes the setup and maintenance of product page style and SKU level information in the PIM system. Internal merchandizing teams provide product to be included for each customer. In this role this position must be able to interact with the business team to understand the scope and navigate multiple existing systems to collect required information to be loaded into the PIM environment.
 

  Responsibilities

Extraction of data from business systems necessary to support the B2B site requirements.
Determine what SKU data is new and what is already setup in PIM.
Create import files that can be loaded into PIM to start the Style and SKU development process.
Access multiple sources to acquire necessary information and load into the PIM Environment.
Assemble weekly update report for department manager.
Participate in team meetings to discuss current and future customer additions and timing requirements.
Leverage external Excel documents to organize data when possible, prior to upload in the PIM environment.



  Skills & Requirements

A minimum of 3+ years overall experience in product data management activities doing data analysis, creation, maintenance and governance of data.
Strong understanding of Excel and how to perform vlookups to merge data from multiple sources.
The aspirant will have to demonstrate very good interpersonal and relationship management skills having worked in a team environment.
Experience working with Product owners, Product Data Managers to clarify requirements.
Demonstrated ability to solve problems.
Should be detail oriented and possess analytical and problem-solving skills.
Highly self-motivated and organized to achieve target release dates.
Good communication skills verbal and written (English).

 Position Summary: We have an exciting opportunity to join our team as a Data Analyst.   The Department of Population Health at NYU School of Medicine seeks a Data Analyst to support the Health Dashboard Initiative (HDI). The analyst will support a growing group of national interactive websites that track health and health-related metrics, including the City Health Dashboard (www.cityhealthdashboard.com) and Congressional District Health Dashboard (www.congressionaldistricthealthdashboard.org). This will involve working with data at the federal, congressional district, county, city, census tract, and census block levels; aggregating geographic data; and calculating robust health metrics that align with administrative boundaries. We are specifically seeking an analyst to support our geospatial and novel metric development work. The analyst should have R programming skills.
We are a dynamic and diverse team that values collaboration, growth, and passion for public health. We strive to be a supportive environment that encourages team members to maintain high standards for the quality of their work while also maintaining a balance with other life priorities. We believe that high-performing teams include people from different backgrounds, and we actively seek a diverse pool of applicants, including those from historically marginalized groups.
 Job Responsibilities:


Retrieving, analyzing, and evaluating health metric data parsed to various geographic boundaries for use in HDI websites with attention to issues of sample size, bias, and timeliness
Assisting in the development, calculation, and validation of new health-related metrics
Exploring new geospatial calculation methods, monitoring administrative boundary updates, and generating geographic boundaries for metric calculation
Documenting workflows and methodological challenges to generating health metric estimates across various geographies
Regularly presenting analytic processes and results to other team members
Assisting in preparing communication materials, blogs, journal articles, reports, and policy briefs
Other administrative, analytic, or research tasks as necessary


 Minimum Qualifications: To qualify you must have a A masters degree in a related field (biostatistics, epidemiology, public health) or equivalent combination of education and experience Skill and experience in the R statistical programming software Demonstrated interest in public health and health equity Experience and interest in working with various types of geospatial data and performing common spatial manipulations (intersects, centroids, reprojections, buffers, etc.). Ability to perform basic statistical and descriptive analyses Ability and interest in working respectfully, reliably, and collaboratively with other team members on multiple projects
 Preferred Qualifications: 2-3 years' work, internship, or project experience in an analytics role  Familiarity with U.S. administrative geographies (counties, congressional districts, consolidated and incorporated places, census tracts etc.)  Familiarity with commonly used public health metrics Experience in R tidyverse packages, writing functions in R, SQL, and GitLab/GitHub Ability to read manuscripts and technical documents and assess the validity of methodological approaches An attitude of creative and collective problem solving and openness to new ideas  Ability to be detail-oriented, organized, and take initiative on projects
 Qualified candidates must be able to effectively communicate with all levels of the organization.  NYU Grossman School of Medicine provides its staff with far more than just a place to work. Rather, we are an institution you can be proud of, an institution where you'll feel good about devoting your time and your talents. Exell Water Company is looking for a results-oriented entry-level team member who demonstrates outstanding data analytic and organizational abilities!
Job Summary: The Data Analyst is responsible for performing various analytical tasks including collecting, cleaning, and analyzing data to provide valuable insights within the organization. This role involves identifying trends, making recommendations based on data, and helping the company optimize its' operations. Will also be responsible for inventory management while providing administrative support to the General Manager.
Essential Functions and Responsibilities:

Lives and models BROWN VALUES in everything we do.
Collecting and analyzing data to help the company make informed decisions.
Will use databases, spreadsheets, APIs, web scraping, or other data extraction methods.
Revise data to ensure its accuracy, completeness, and consistency.
Effectively manage missing data and outliers.
Responsible for inventory management, for instance, verifying the warehouse inventory and placing orders for all Exell products.
Apply statistical and analytical techniques to explore data sets, identify trends, correlations, and patterns, and extract actionable insights.
Prepare and deliver regular and as needed reports or visuals (charts, graphs, etc.), summarizing key findings and insights to support decision-making processes.
Maintain data banks and ensure data integrity and security. Implement data governance and data quality standards.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including revenue manager, senior leadership, and department managers, to understand data requirements and address business challenges.
Stay updated with industry trends, tools, and best practices in data analysis and data science.
Identify opportunities for process improvement and efficiency through data analysis.

Physical Demands:

Ability to remain stationary for prolonged periods of time.
Continually operate a computer and other electronic devices.

Work Environment:

Work is performed in an office environment.






   Qualifications
  




Qualifications:

Valid driver’s license and approved driving record.
Bachelor’s degree in related field (business, statistics, accounting, etc).
Strong written communication skills and ability to interact with customers and managers.
Strong skills in Microsoft excel program with knowledge of v look up, macros and formulas.
Proficient with all Microsoft office programs.

Job Summary:



About The Role
The Marketing Analytics team is seeking a Senior Analyst to support our core marketing measurement, automation and reporting needs. The Senior Analyst will collaborate closely with Hulu Marketing, Data Engineering, Data Architecture, Data Product, Data Science, and Finance teams. Their focus will be on developing tools, optimizations, and key business insights to propel Hulu’s growth. The ideal candidate will possess a passion for both digital and linear media landscapes and a deep understanding of each step in the marketing journey.
 Responsibilities

Create, deliver and continuously improve our business measurement solutions
Partner closely with business stakeholders to identify and unlock opportunities
Use internal and external analytics tools, SQL, and scripting languages to access and analyze multivariate data
Analyze and report key data quality health KPIs through regular metric monitoring and revise as needed as the number of datasets and critical systems expand
Translate complex reporting needs into technical specifications, including calculations, custom groups, parameters, filtering criteria and/or aggregations
Analyze subscriber and behavior data to identify patterns, uncover opportunities, and create common understanding of how people are interacting with the platform and content
Partner with our Product, Engineering and QE team to build and automate reports and dashboards that provide insights into business measurement and effectiveness
Build intuitive presentations, interfaces, infographics and visualizations to create a data-driven narrative in partnership with our Strategic Planning and Marketing stakeholders
Provide ongoing reporting and analysis to inform and support business, product and marketing decisions

 Basic Qualifications

BA or BS in Business, Math/Statistics, Economics, CS, Engineering, or related
5+ years of hands-on analytical work experience with SQL
Expertise manipulating large data sets, interpreting data trends and using a multitude of disparate data sources and tools
Experience with creating, executing and analyzing complex AB/MVT test constructs in order to test stakeholder hypotheses
Strong analytical skills with the ability to apply business strategy to data analysis and recommendations
Strong experience in documenting the data requirements, data strategy, data rules (standardization, cleanse, and validation)
Strong analytical and technical skills to troubleshoot issues, analyze the cause, quickly come-up with the possible solutions, document the changes, and communicate organizational impact
Ability to evaluate risks and provide recommendations in a timely manner
Explain data anomalies, develop data visualizations and reporting to drive key messaging and recommendations using tools such as Tableau and Looker
Ability to think strategically, analyze and interpret market and consumer information

Preferred Qualifications

Experience in the streaming media industry or other subscription-based service
Experience in the technology industry, knowledge of data products
Experience writing, managing and deploying Python code
Familiarity with data platforms and applications such as Databricks, Datorama, Snowflake, Redshift, Airflow, Tableau

 Additional Information
#DISNEYTECH

 The hiring range for this position in Santa Monica, CA is $114,900 to $154,100 per year, and in New York, NY is $120,400 - $161,500 per year. The base pay actually offered will take into account internal equity and also may vary depending on the candidate’s geographic region, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience among other factors. A bonus and/or long-term incentive units may be provided as part of the compensation package, in addition to the full range of medical, financial, and/or other benefits, dependent on the level and position offered.

The Data Analyst will execute the production, analysis, and dissemination of customer and operational metrics to key business stakeholders. You get a thrill out of turning data into actionable information to make a big impact across the organization. You enjoy breaking down the hairiest of problems and sharing your insights with key stakeholders across the organization, and recommending sound business decisions based on insights from the underlying data– your analysis is that good. Although data is important, you always keep the customer front of mind and enjoy optimizing the customer experience, which translates to creating long-term business value. Lastly, you’re ready to join a fast and flat organization where much is expected of you because you have what it takes to influence real change. You’ll enjoy the journey just as much as the outcome, and your positive demeanor will influence others along the way to do the same.
May include:

Deeply understand our organization's data structure and look for ways to improve it to enhance our ability to perform robust data analysis.
Deeply understand all sources of data across the enterprise, link to data strategy, and continually evolve the ability to measure and track key data points to enable data-driven decisions
Evaluate the effectiveness and financial impact of marketing programs and promotional activities.
Collect and provide quantitative and qualitative information to measure the effectiveness of marketing activities and answer strategic business questions
Track performance and create KPIs of targeted programs offered to customers to help drive better results
Gather and analyze the external market and economic data to better understand correlations to industry and business activity and provide regular insights
Utilize BI solutions to improve the timeliness of data and better visibility to decision-makers to help them monitor, measure, or predict how the company is performing
Assist with maintenance and management of the Marketing SQL database.
Perform marketing research & analysis to inform customer targeting & segmentation, and tracking of Customer Lifetime Value across the enterprise
Enable Voice of Customer (VOC) data collection, tracking, and analysis to improve Customer Experience at all levels – end consumer (homeowner), contractor (dealer), and distributor
Understand current and target Customer Experience and Customer Journey; create a dashboard to continually measure key metrics to understand gaps and areas that need further attention and investment
Create new data sets when there is little or no data available, to inform marketing analysis
Work hand-in-hand with Marketing, Sales, Operations, Finance, Logistics, and IT to identify new data sets and how those can be used to bring value to the market and company; engaged third-party vendors and customers as needed.
Engage with third-party data providers to strengthen data models as needed
Assist with internal assessments of workflow processes to identify inefficiencies, especially those where Marketing is involved, and propose more efficient processes and procedures
Provide data and ad hoc analysis to support marketing managers as needed
Perform additional projects/duties to support ongoing business needs.

Nature & Scope:

Possesses a broad theoretical job knowledge typically obtained through advanced education.
Has no discretion to deviate from established procedures by performing structured work assignments.
Work is closely supervised.
Problems faced are not typically difficult or complex.
Explains facts, policies, and practices related to the job area.

Knowledge & Skills:

Strong data storytelling ability – the ability to produce actionable information/insights, not just data crunching
Ability to put results into context, considering the overall business goals and performance.
Eager to make a big impact at a large company – you show up for work and get things done
Comfortable with experimentation and testing of Minimum Viable Products to determine if proposed business models/solutions scale up
Proficient in MS Office, especially Excel, and Access; ability to translate data insights into PowerPoint presentations
Proficient with BI tools such as Tableau, DOMO, or Microsoft BI
Experience with Qualtrics or other survey tools
Understanding of relational databases with experience in SQL or R preferred
Natural ability and desire to work on a team; goes the extra mile when needed
Ability to work independently.
Excellent communication skills, both verbally and written, capable of communicating with people of many different levels of an organization
Great analytical skills with attention to detail
Ability to grasp complex concepts and systems quickly.
Ability to manage multiple projects and shift direction quickly.
Intellectual curiosity and strong passion for using data to solve problems.
Ability to apply good judgment, strong work ethic, and integrity on the job.

Competencies:
Experience:

0-3 years of work experience in a Marketing / BI Analyst role
Proven experience as a BI Analyst working with eCommerce, retail, marketing, and/or web development applications.
Experience solving complex business problems involving a heavy amount of analytics.
Digital Marketing-based experience preferred.
HVAC industry experience preferred but not required

Education/Certification

Bachelor’s degree in Marketing / Business / Engineering / Statistics / Mathematics / Economics; or another related degree with a strong quantitative emphasis
(Optional) Master’s degree in Business Administration / Marketing

People Management: No
Physical Requirements / Work Environment:

Must be able to perform essential responsibilities with or without reasonable accommodations

Reports To:

Sr. Mgr., Strategic Analytics & Insights (i.e., Head of Strategic Analytics and Insights Dept.)

Qualified Applicants must be legally authorized for employment in the United States. Qualified applicants will not require employer sponsored work authorization now or in the future for employment in the United States. Summary


The Sr. Data Analyst will provide senior-level support and analysis for KCNSC enterprise data projects, define processes, and adhere to them. The role is responsible for performing data analysis, data mapping, data integration, data quality, and application development for our data cataloging solution. This role will provide primary support to be focused around our Data Governance activities as determined by KCNSC Data Office management.




 Duties and Responsibilities



Utilize analytical and technical skills for translating and analyzing business needs into requirements and lead the design and implementation of ourgovernance solutions (cataloging, data quality, access management)
Work with project work streams, business stakeholders to design, implement and maintain best practice data governance cataloging and data quality solutionsto support the business.
Perform data analysis by querying data sets in databases, spreadsheets, semi-structured data, and flat file format to identify and document master data, reference data, transaction data, business rules, data integration rules, data mapping and transformations.
Document internal processes and audit procedures to ensure data integrity of solutions
Research and resolve unexpected results or internal process flaws. Effectively prioritize and deploy solutions that can replace manual process
Develop our application design and use for our data cataloging and data quality systems
Support development of master data, data cataloging and data quality processes in data management tools.
Support a variety of information management projects of a highly varied nature including data analysis, data mining and data optimization
Develop and follow standard operating procedures for regularly occurring processes
Mentor, Cross-train and provide back-up coverage to other team members when needed
Operating at the Sr Analyst level, duties/responsibilities should be carried out with autonomy and require minimal direct supervision of day-to-day tasks and only high-level direction from departmental leadership. Should have the ability to support and coach others while maintaining productivity on directly assigned work.





 You Must Have



Bachelors Degree or 6 years equivalent experience
5 years of demonstrated data management experience, including the ability to merge, clean and analyze large amounts of data
3 years of demonstrated experience with application development of cataloging and/or data quality solutions





 We Value




Technical experience should include SQL, PL/SQL, T/SQL, NoSQL programming, and database objects such as stored procedures, materialized views, functions etc. or analytics tools (Microstrategy, Tableau, PowerBI) or data management tools (MDM, Data Catalog, Data Quality tools).
Data Process Analysis experience should include documentation and analysis techniques such as data flow diagrams (DFD), Unified Modeling Language (UML), and analyzing system level information flow and decomposing data process dependencies within a digital ecosystem.
Experience working with Data management platforms (Collibra, Informatica, Denodo, etc.)
Experience working with data models, data warehouse, data management and data movement.
Demonstrated ability to manage through ambiguity and competing priorities.
Excellent oral and written communication and analytical skills. Strong interpersonal and collaborative work style.
Ability to work with and manage confidential information in a professional manner.
Strong organizational and time management skills. Ability to lead/drive priorities.
Experience working on large scale business process improvement with results.
Ability to translate business requirements into effective process management solutions.
Proactive analytical and collaborative problem-solving skills with business acumen.
Ability to clearly document business process & system requirements.
Ability to communicate effectively with both senior managerial and technical teams.
Ability to drive action, deliver results, with agile approach.
Convey information with clarity and directness, ensuring the message is understood across diverse, global teams.

 Title of Position: Process and Data Analyst I
 Position Type: Full-Time. Regular hours include Monday to Friday 8:00AM – 5:00PM
 Compensation Range: $28.00/hr. - $36.50/hr. *Hiring rates may be dependent on a number of factors, including years of directly related work experience, education, geographic location or special skills*
 Location: Hybrid/Remote opportunity for candidates residing ONLY in NY, NJ or PA
 Responsibilities/Duties:

You will partner with stakeholders to elicit business requirements and assist in the implementation of process improvement and process re-engineering projects.
You will be a contributor in productively moving work through the requirements-to-release pipeline. You will act as the liaison between technical development and project stakeholders to facilitate communication, consistency, and maintain project scope.
You will be responsible for conducting process audits and performance assessments on new and existing solutions to ensure effectiveness.
You will also provide training and support to team members to ensure that best practices are followed.

Minimum Qualifications & Experience:

An associate degree required with 1-3 years of related process improvement experience. 3-5 years of relevant experience will be considered in lieu of a degree.

Competency in project management and process re-engineering using a combination of related tools and other technologies is expected.
Proficient in the Microsoft Office Suite programs.
Proficient with standard office equipment such as computers, phones, photocopiers, filing cabinets and fax machines, PCs, etc.
Visions remains committed to the aspects of diversity and inclusion and will consider alternative education and experience.


Preferred Qualifications & Experience:

Bachelor’s degree preferred.

Certification in Lean Six Sigma Green Belt or equivalent.
Symitar infrastructure or other financial industry core platform.

Do you want to help empower employers, employees, and retirees to better navigate the changing world of benefits? Are you looking to provide a tailored, integrated experience that combines benefit consulting expertise with innovative, user-centered technology? Do you want to be part of a team that values collaboration and diversity and invests in your personal and professional growth? If so, we have an exciting opportunity for you to join WTW as a Business Analyst 2, where you will apply your technical knowledge, analytical, and problem-solving skills to provide benefits administration solutions and services to Fortune 500 companies.

The Role 

Understands different system functionalities and dependencies
Learns and applies WTW best practices, standards, and tools
Performs system configuration based on the requirements

  JOB DESCRIPTION
 

  You're an original. So are we.
 


  We're a company of people who like to forge our own path. We invented the blue jean in 1873, and we reinvented khaki pants in 1986. We pioneered labor and environmental guidelines in manufacturing. And we work to build sustainability into everything we do. Our brands stand for freedom and self-expression around the world.
 


  Where we lead, others follow. For more than 160 years, we've used the strength of our brands to lead with our values and make an outsized impact on the world. We employ more than 15,000 people globally to support our great brands: Levi's®, Dockers®, Denizen®, Signature by Levi Strauss & Co.™ and Beyond Yoga.
 


  Within center demand planning, the global size analytics team is dedicated to understanding product selling at the size level across all brands, categories, genders, channels, and customers. Given the size-intensive nature of the product we sell and the complex network of points of sale, understanding our performance at a size and store level is important to the success of Levi Strauss & Co. The Size Planning team works to build accurate size profiles and size strategies to maximize revenues through optimized investment.
 


  Reporting into the Global Sizing Digital & Analytics Lead, the Size Data Analyst will be the main point person for all sizing activities. You will own the size level production signal and be responsible for the strategic direction of the size forecast including risk and opportunity identification and action. You will coordinate key strategic initiatives in both strategy and process. You will work cross-functionally across the organization to support and drive the sizing inputs and perspectives that achieve the broader company goals.
 


  This role is based in San Francisco and will work onsite three days per week.
 


  About the Job:
 

Create size profiles using SAS and related tools for specific product segments and locations
Produce impactful analytics that drive meaningful business discussions and actions to enhance size productivity, inventory efficiency, and financial results
Utilize data to drive size decisions (size offerings and profiles). Create and maintain any reports/analysis to provide hindsight/insight to relevant team to maximize inventory investment returns by identifying, analyzing, communicating, influencing, and delivering insight
Partner with Merchandising, Sales, Allocation, Inventory Management, and Merchandise Planning teams to drive effective size grid strategies
Gain in-depth product and area-specific knowledge to provide informed analysis, recommendations, and support key business decisions on size offerings
Respond to sizing requests based on business needs, including size grid changes and size-out investigations
Align activities and timelines with the GTM process and planning milestones. Communicate key sizing deliverables and timings cross-functionally, including follow-ups
Serve as a subject-matter expert on all sizing tools. Train users on sizing tools and systems, providing ongoing support
Own all size signal deliverables and ensure size profile accuracy, by partnering with cross functional team to deliver pre-season and in-season sizing activities and analysis required
Review and validate machine learning size profiles and provide input to data scientists to enhance the ML model. Participate in user acceptance testing to facilitate the development of digital sizing tools



  About You:
 

Bachelor’s degree in business, Economics, Communications, Statistics, Data analytics, Computer science or a related field
Minimum 3 years of experience in merchandise retailing or demonstrated abilities in merchandise planning
High proficiency with Microsoft PowerPoint and Excel, with the ability to quickly learn technical applications. Medium proficiency in Tableau and Power BI, and a basic understanding of SQL and Python is required
Analytical skills, attention to detail, and a high degree of ownership. Ability to interpret meaningful themes from quantitative data
Ability to present ideas and directions clearly to others
Skillful in data visualization and storytelling to present ideas

 Description: 
 Job Summary:
The Business Intelligence Analyst will be responsible for, but not limited to, gathering and analyzing operational data for the organization and supporting management and leadership with the data analytics necessary to make informed and objective business and policy decisions.
Candidates must be proficient in building, maintaining, navigating, analyzing & automating databases. Candidates must possess advanced Excel skills and the knowledge needed to accurately collect valid and reliable data, process, and analyze such data to support business initiatives, which will drive informed decision-making across the organization. Candidates will exhibit attention to detail, initiative, organizational skills, excellent communication skills as well as the ability to manage time effectively. This role requires a blend of technical expertise, leadership skills, and can turn complex data sets into actionable insights. A background in nonprofit, health, or education data and familiarity with CARF accreditation is highly preferred.
 Key Responsibilities:

 Data Management:

Leverage understanding of Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities (CARF) accreditation standards to analyze outcomes and ensure compliance with healthcare and rehabilitation benchmarks
Support in the collection, processing, and storage of data, including deep diving into data, mapping processes and problems
Conduct data cleansing activities to ensure accuracy and completeness of data within the company's databases
Ensure data integrity, reliability, accuracy, and security
Support the implementation & maintenance of data governance policies
Apply knowledge of IEP (Individualized Education Programs) data requirements and outcomes to ensure compliance with special education reporting standards

Analysis and Reporting:

Analyze data, with a focus on risk & opportunity management, to identify patterns, trends, and insights
Apply out-of-the-box thinking to solve problems, improve processes, and drive results
Present findings and insights to internal customers to support informed decision making
Prepare, distribute, or deliver weekly/monthly data analytics & business intelligence reports that identify, explain, and evaluate problems and available solutions
Provide solution recommendations to solve internal customer needs, testing & implementing chosen solutions into daily processes
Create visualizations and dashboards to facilitate understanding of data trends.
Incorporate insights from AOP (Annual Operating Plan) budget analysis to align financial performance with operational and strategic goals
Utilize advanced Excel formulas and Pivot Tables to efficiently analyze and summarize large data sets, improving decision-making and reporting visibility

Strategy and Planning:

Support Executive & Business Leadership with identifying key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure data project success

Tools and Technologies:

Utilize data analytics tools and technologies
Proficiency in using analytics tools such as Pivot Tables, advanced Excel formulas and Tableau

Stakeholder Engagement:

Work closely with various departments to understand their data needs and challenges
Provide data-driven recommendations to improve business operations and outcomes
Collaborate with teams to ensure that data analysis supports CARF accreditation requirements, AOP budget alignment, and compliance

Requirements: 
 
Education:

Bachelor’s degree in Health Management, Business Analytics, Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or a related field. Master’s level degree in stated disciplines preferred

Experience:

Minimum of 1 - 3 years of experience in data analysis or a related field
Demonstrated ability to manage complex data projects from inception to completion

Technical Skills:

Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or similar
Strong understanding of statistical methods and data modeling

Soft Skills:

Excellent communication and presentation skills
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities
Ability to work successfully in an ambiguous environment, meet tight deadlines and prioritize workload even when faced with conflicting priorities
Applies out-of-the-box thinking to solve problems, improve processes, and help drive results.

Must be a US Citizen and be located or relocate to in the Wichita, Kansas area.

  Junior Financial and Data Analyst
 The Claremont Colleges Services (TCCS) is the central coordinating and support organization for a highly regarded cluster of seven independent colleges known as The Claremont Colleges. TCCS, with about 300 staff members, provides exceptional shared services to 9,000 students, and almost 3,600 faculty and staff. TCCS staff work in both student-facing services as well as administrative and operational services. Our numerous departments are located throughout The Claremont Colleges campus in the beautiful city of Claremont, California.  ABOUT THE POSITION:  Purpose: A versatile team member skilled in delivering a wide range of accounting services to The Claremont Colleges Services (TCCS) and The Claremont Colleges (TCC). This role ensures that the internal departments of TCCS receive accurate and timely reports. Responsibilities include budget preparation, general accounting, internal financial reporting, and non-financial data collection. The individual in this position effectively balances independent and collaborative work, handles confidential information with discretion, and is proficient in managing tasks within the Workday system to support TCCS's overall budget model.  ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS  The following are the fundamental duties and responsibilities of this position which the incumbent must be able to perform to fulfill the purpose and requirements of this position.  Accounting

Assists in preparing weekly, monthly, and quarterly journal entries, and is responsible for reviewing journal entries and Supplier Invoices in Workday.
Prepares recurring and ad hoc journal entries and inputs institutional TCCS Supplier Invoices in Workday.
Supports the creation, review, and discussion of monthly Budget to Actual reports for TCCS departments and senior management.
Collaborates closely with the Office of Financial Services to ensure seamless coordination of accounting activities.
Acts as a 'superuser' for the financial system, using expertise to develop meaningful reports and provide training to TCCS internal departments. Assists with managing Worktags - keywords or dimensions used in Workday to categorize and describe transactions and events for reporting and security purposes.
Provides customer service by assisting departments with accounting and budget inquiries. Reviews transactions to ensure accurate accounting classification and proper supporting documentation, in line with TCCS policies.
 Budget

Assists in the preparation of the annual budget, including setup, data collection, and providing support to directors during budget development, ensuring timeliness and effectiveness of the process.
Provides customer service by assisting departments and intercollegiate programs with budget-related questions.
 Data Analysis

Assists management in developing and maintaining organization-wide metrics and data collection processes.
Collects data from TCCS Departments, TCC Colleges, and TCC Programs, ensuring data quality and application accuracy for departments, providing reliable analyses with a high degree of confidence.
Generates recurring metrics reports (monthly, quarterly, annually) for various stakeholders, accurately informing them about the utilization and outcomes of current strategic initiatives.
Produces relevant graphs and charts, drafts narratives for reports to upper management, designs reports to integrate data, and provides regular updates on customer and operational data, with a focus on progress against targets and service level agreements.
  QUALIFICATIONS  Education/Training: A bachelor's degree in accounting, business administration, or a related field; or the equivalent in a combination of education, training, and additional work experience beyond the minimum required.  Experience:

At least two (2) years of experience in accounting and financial reporting. Experience using cloud-based ERP systems is required.
  
  Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities: 

Proficiency in MS Excel, Word, Outlook, Powerpoint, Teams and Adobe PDF required; strong Microsoft Excel knowledge required. 
Foundational understanding of GAAP.
Fundamental understanding of and familiarity with maintaining confidentiality of sensitive information.
Ability to solve problems and work with limited direction
Strong verbal, and written communication in English.
Ability to summarize data in a clear and concise manner and communicate effectively to different stakeholders.
Strong interpersonal skill with the ability to foster collaboration and build positive relationships with internal and external constituencies, including with customers and vendors.
Strong analytical skills with an ability to synthesize and effectively articulate data.
Ability to manage time and assignments to meet expectations and strict deadlines.
Flexibility and comfort adjusting to changing priorities and challenges.
Demonstrate maturity, tact, openness to new ideas and change, resiliency, and composure in difficult and unexpected circumstances.
A service-oriented approach to individuals at all levels and across all disciplines and campuses.
High dedication to professionalism and ethical behavior always at all levels of the organization.
Commitment to always delivering excellent customer services and support.
Able and willing to learn new systems and technologies as needed.
  Preferred Qualifications:

Workday experience
Qualtrics experience
Tableau experience
IPEDS knowledge
Experience in business office and administrative support functions.
Experience in Higher Education or other complex organizations

Ability to work well with and establish trust with diverse individuals in roles across TCC and TCCS
Organized, acute attention to detail

Ability to solve problems and work with limited direction

Job Description Summary
Performs entry-level data analysis and data research work within the Texas Water Development Board’s (TWDB) Technical Systems Oversight (TSO) department. Work involves conducting analysis of and research on data, providing results, visualizing data, and monitoring and implementing data quality. Work involves analyzing and reporting on the TWDB’s financial assistance and project information maintained within TxWISE, the agency-wide database. Identifies and interprets data patterns and trends and assesses data quality following standard procedures. Works within cross-divisional, cross-office teams in routine data gathering and analysis projects. Assists with building and maintaining visual tools and dashboard systems, including queries and reports. Assists other staff in the TSO team in completing and implementing long-term projects. Works under close supervision and under the guidance of the TSO team’s Senior Data Analyst, with minimal latitude for the use of initiative and independent judgment. Reports to the Manager of the Technical Systems Oversight Department.
Essential Job Functions

Writes and run queries for data collection, extraction, and analysis using SQL-based programs and other data analytic software.
Responds to requests for information on an ad hoc basis for internal and external customers.
Contributes to and assist in maintaining a library of data analysis tools, queries, databases, and reports for the Technical Systems Oversight (TSO) team.
Assists with developing software applications or programming as a means for improvements in operational efficiencies.
Documents desktop procedures related to routine tasks and standard procedures.
Works with cross-divisional teams to collaborate on long-term projects.
Assists other staff of the TSO team in completing and implementing long-term projects and agency initiatives.
Collects, produce, and maintain supporting documentation for data analysis and projects and maintain standards of source documents.
Maintains confidential and sensitive information.
Ensures individual and team files (electronic and hard versions) are appropriately maintained and timely disposed of in accordance with the agency’s records retention procedures and schedule.
Maintains required certifications and licenses and meets the continuing education needs and requirements of the position to include attending mandatory training courses.
May be required to operate a state or personal vehicle for business purposes.
Performs other duties as assigned.

Minimum Qualifications.

Graduation from an accredited four-year college or university with a bachelor's degree in Data Science, Business Analytics, Computer or Information Science, Statistics, Social or Political Science, Planning, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering, Business, Finance, or other related fields.
Relevant work experience in data analysis, business analysis, or related field.
Relevant education and experience can be substituted for each other on a year-for-year basis

Preferred Qualifications

One or more years of progressive work experience with financial assistance programs, procurements, and/or grants within the water industry, engineering field, finance industry, a governmental agency, and/or another related industry.
Experience with SQL Server Management Studio, or similar software, building queries and reports.
Experience building tables and manipulating data with Microsoft Excel.
State agency database data entry experience.

Knowledge, Skills, and Abilities (KSAs)

Knowledge of local, state, and federal laws and regulations relevant to the Technical Systems Oversight (TSO) Department.
Knowledge of the principles and practices of public administration.
Knowledge of financial systems, word processing, database querying, and spreadsheets.
Knowledge of the structure and content of the English language including the meaning and spelling of words, rules of composition, and grammar.
Knowledge of state and federal financial assistance programs.
Skills in using Microsoft Office programs such as Word, Excel, and Access.
Skills in use of internet, email, word processing, spreadsheet, presentation, and database software.
Skills in using Microsoft Teams, Project, Planner, and other organization software applications.
Skills in identifying complex problems and reviewing related information to develop and evaluate options and implement solutions.
Skills in interpersonal communications and the ability to interact effectively with a wide variety of customers and stakeholders.

Ability to communicate effectively both verbally and in writing.

Health Services Data Analyst - (24142619)





 HEALTH SERVICES DATA ANALYST


 RESEARCH ANALYTICS AND PLANNING BUREAU


 HELENA, MT


 MISSION - Montana Department of Corrections is creating a safer Montana through Accountability, Rehabilitation and Empowerment.
If you want to work making positive changes in the community the Montana Department of Corrections is the place for you!

 JOB OVERVIEW - Research, develop and apply techniques to collect, analyze, and report quantitative and non-quantitative health care information that assists health executives, providers, and administrators’ managers, accounting, or other professionals make data-driven, strategic decisions, reduce health care costs, deliver better care, and overall have a positive impact on people’s lives.

Responsible for modifying and updating data collection or statistical models based on changing or differing industry standards, needs of requesters, projects, or programs.
Coordinate, collaborate, and communicate within an agency or business unit on research projects.
Coordinate research and statistics with other operations and functions of the agency or business unit. Analyze and integrate various data sources and factors to produce projections or trends.
Prepare research reports containing descriptive, analytical, and evaluative content, including recommendations.
Works as part of the RAP Bureau with a primary focus on healthcare data and projects.
Assist and support other data analysis needs of the department.

Types of data sources to be analyzed:

Clinical data: The most common type of health care data analytics is clinical data. This includes using electronic health records (EHRs) to directly improve medical outcomes.
Claims data: Health Services Data Analysts will analyze claims data to help institutions identify trends in treatment which could provide critical financial readiness and planning.
Pharmaceutical data: Data could include pharmaceutical trends, expenses, and healthcare decision making.
Behavioral data: Data specific to mental health and mental disorders, pharmaceutical interventions, behavioral interventions, suicide, and substance use.
Public health data: A health services data analyst might work with public health data to deliver statistics, infographics, and reports after identifying methods for preventing disease or promoting health within a population.


This position is a hybrid position located in Helena, MT with at least two days in the office.

About the Company
Origin is a digital consultancy providing professional services specializing in Analytics, AI, and Application Modernization solutions, to achieve our client’s digital transformation goals. We are a team of passionate and humble technology enthusiasts who maintain a high level of integrity and are looking to enhance the team with those for whom these values are central as well. We are focused on building a team of collaborators who are looking for a fast-paced environment, an inclusive culture that allows all team members to flourish and achieve their full potential. Help us build a company that delivers on this promise and create a fun and exciting workplace for all our colleagues.
Fueled by the advances in technology, and the strategic investments that our clients are making in digital transformation, the services we provide are in high demand as we solve our client’s complex business problems. At Origin you will have an opportunity to work on the leading edge with emerging technologies, and on projects that will make a real impact in the business world. We look forward to the unique perspectives and experiences you will bring to help achieve our common goals and deliver impactful solutions for our clients.
The Opportunity
We are currently seeking a Data & Analytics Leader with a track record of having guided large data transformations and advanced analytics implementations. This role will be responsible for defining the go to market offerings and building a team that is responsible for data strategy and governance, data science, data engineering, and delivering insight driven advanced analytics dashboards and reports to clients.
While the primary focus for the Leader will be to build out the Insights and Analytics offering capabilities, this leader will also support data initiatives for both the AI and Application Modernization offerings and will need to provide thought leadership to ensure successful delivery of projects for these two offerings. The Leader will also develop collateral to support the sales process and will be assisting in a pre-sale’s capacity for qualified opportunities.
The Leader will guide clients through strategy, design, and implementation to achieve their data transformation goals. The Leader will collaborate with the Technology Leader ensure that the offering is well aligned with current client needs and with an eye on advancements in this space.
The Leader will be responsible for building the team needed to deliver the capabilities and guide and mentor the team, ensuring that they have the right skills to deliver high impact services to our clients.
The Leader will also have primary responsibility for staying connected with certain named clients and ensuring client satisfaction for project outcomes by defining, applying and measuring solution delivery quality. The role is a hands-on role where the Leader will be responsible for engaging directly in client engagements and will lead teams to deliver on the projects.
The Leader will be responsible for effectively measuring the performance of the practice team members and ensuring that practice utilization rates are at an optimal level to ensure profitability for the practice as team members are being hired.
The Leader will support an innovation agenda with a goal of proposing practical solutions that focuses on relevant data, integrated in novel ways, coupled with analytics to achieve digital transformation.
Key Responsibilities
The Data and Analytics Leader will be a key member of the leadership team with the following responsibilities:
Technical Understanding

Be an expert across data strategy and governance, data science, data engineering, and delivering insight driven advanced analytics dashboards and build a brand internally and externally for Origin in the Data and Analytics solutions arena.

· Possess detailed competency and understanding in the Data and Analytics space with a track record of having guided large data transformations and advanced analytics implementations for small and large customers.
· Ability to define a data strategy and guide clients on a roadmap to achieve success with data transformation projects, which include migrations, dashboards, Artificial Intelligence, and Application Modernization projects.
· Ability to lead and drive client conversations and arrive at the right solutions for client needs.
· Knowledge of the Microsoft and Databricks platforms and how to leverage their capabilities to deliver on the project needs.
Business Development
· Expertise in the Data and Analytics space to be able to help guide client conversations and position Origin as the trusted advisor to the client.
· Ability to establish trust and build relationships with the clients in order to position Origin as the service provider of choice for new and existing customers.
· Ability to leverage current network and build new connections to generate new business opportunities and drive a pipeline of work for Origin.
· Identify "follow-on" sales opportunities at existing clients to establish a recurring revenue and customers for life.
· Assist with proposal efforts including completing project scoping, estimation, and pricing to position Origin to win in competitive situations.
· Complete SOW assessments to ensure that contracts are well scoped and thoughtfully estimated and position Origin to receive revenue for all the work that needs to be performed.
Team Development
· Recruit and mentor team members who are culturally aligned and are top performers in their field to ensure we can deliver on every project successfully.
· Identify the right team structure to ensure team members are clear on their roles and are highly productive to maximize profitability.
· Partner with the HR team to put a competitive team member engagement strategy in place to maintain a high level of team member retention.
· Develop training plans to ensure that team members stay on the cutting edge of technology needed to support Origin’s project work and are poised for personal growth.
· Conduct effective performance evaluations and maintain high standards, mentoring those with less experience through formal and informal channels and taking action when necessary.
Delivery Focused
· Extensive experience in a technology consulting environment juggling multiple clients and projects and providing oversight over a large portfolio of projects.
· Experience stepping into a client facing role to provide air cover to team and swarming projects that are faced with issues and need to be rescued.
· Provide subject matter expertise and be a trusted advisor to teams and client stakeholders. Project confidence and ensure that things will get done right when delivering project work.
· Ensure that learnings form client engagements result in continuous improvements of internal processes/assets to ensure consistency and repeatability across clients.
Client Management
· Develop lasting relationships with client stakeholders and team members that foster a sense of loyalty.
· Communicate effectively with clients to identify and understand client needs and the ability to position Origin services to satisfy the needs.
· Maintain active relationships with clients and continuously seek opportunities to increase customer satisfaction and deepening relationships.
Financial Management
· Firm understanding of P&L and how to manage a lean team model to ensure high profitability and investing in the right areas for growth.
· Implement processes to ensure a clear view of project financials and cost-to-completion projections and making the right decisions to ensure client satisfaction while maintaining project profitability.
· Develop and refine delivery models to optimize project delivery for the client.
· Maintain visibility and a clear understanding of revenue forecasts, gross margin, utilization, profitability, and average bill rate movement for the 3-6 month window.
Additional Attributes for Success
The Data and Analytics Leader is a motivated self-starter and an exceptional collaborator. Given that Origin is an early-stage company focused on providing mid-sized and enterprise customers with digital consulting in the data analytics, AI, and application modernization space, the role requires the Leader to be involved with the offering definition, practice building, delivery oversight, and ensuring high client satisfaction through quality deliverables and ensuring project success. Therefore, this person needs to feel comfortable operating in an environment where there will be competing priorities and be able to navigate them with grace.
Beyond being the person who is excited about helping build out the business, this person will need to be excited about contributing to building and fostering a culture that will truly make Origin stand out among its competitors. This person will share the inherent belief that an amazing culture does not happen by accident rather it is thoughtfully developed and nurtured and is the by-product of every team member living out their core values, working through challenges collaboratively and with positive intent, and enjoying each other’s company along the way. We recognize that this is not always easy, but we believe that everyone needs to be the keeper of our culture and this Leader will be willing to be a positive force ensuring that it is a culture that engenders connections.

The Financial Analyst is responsible for but not limited to analyzing grants & contracts, coordinating and executing the budget process (capital and operating), financial analysis, government cost reports, and decision support functions for Gateways. This position will develop reports/information products and provide analysis that supports organizational decision-making through high-level analysis, reporting, research, and effective use of data generated from various sources. He or she will work as part of a team on projects that relate to financial planning and analysis, risk assessment, revenue forecasting, and operational excellence. The Financial Analyst will also be involved in all areas of utilizing data, forecasting, and developing program structures and processes to assure efficient operations and sound outcomes. This position will be called on to work collaboratively with other Managers as well as with Executive-level staff.

 ESSENTIALS DUTIES

Serve as a resource to Senior Management, Operations Directors, Business Office, and staff on revenue cycle performance.
Manage all fiscal activities related to revenue cycle performance to meet short-term strategic goals.
Enhance and standardize work-flow processes throughout the revenue cycle to assist in achieving consistency in maintaining the critical success factors outlined in the agencys standard operating procedures.
Work closely with Director of Business Office/Patient Accounting to ensure accurate patient billing, scheduling and efficient account collection.
Conduct weekly medical, live support, productivity and other related reconciliations to ensure accurate revenue recognition; perform monthly contract utilization and total cost of care (TCOC) analysis.
Set up Accounts Receivable billing schedules, guide Accounts Receivable team on the manual billings and payment reconciliations to ensure the accuracy of the AR aging.
Assist Director of Revenue and Financial Management with financial data analysis; ensure that expenditures are consistently aligned with grant and program budgets throughout the grant & contracts/fund period.
Assist CFO in the annual budgeting and planning process; assist Controller in the audits.
Perform other duties as requested by the CFO and/or Director of Revenue and Financial Management

 EDUCATION & CERTIFICATES

Bachelors degree in Accounting, Finance, Economics, Statistics, Information Systems, Data Science, Computer Science,or related field required.
An equivalent combination of education, training, and experience in a data-centric role may be considered
Master's degree preferred


 EXPERIENCE/QUALIFICATIONS

Minimum two (2) years of progressively responsible financial experience, including Financial Statement prep, benchmarking, reimbursement, cost accounting, and budgeting/forecasting.
Proven experience in healthcare (EHR) data management and data analytics
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to exercise sound judgment and make decisions based on accurate and timely analyses
Must have skills necessary to engage and work with others from diverse backgrounds.
Ability to structure the work, manage the process, drive the right set of analyses, and communicate the answer through a compelling storyline.
High level of integrity and dependability with a strong sense of urgency and results-orientation
Strong interpersonal skills and ability to communicate effectively in English, both verbally and in writing.
Excellent organizational skills
Knowledge of Medicare reimbursement principles is a plus.
Experience in government contract compliance, especially Los Angeles County Department of Mental Health and Californias Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development (OSHPD)
Advanced computer skills including proficiency in MS Office and accounting systems. Microsoft Dynamics, Black baud Financial Edge, and financial reporting software skills are highly desirable.

 REQUIREMENTS

Must pass Department of Justice (DOJ), Federal Bureau of Investigations (FBI), and Community Care Licensing (CCL) background clearance.
Valid California Drivers license.
TB clearance.
Driving record acceptable for coverage by Gateways insurance carrier.
Fire and Safety Training*.
Crisis Prevention Institute Training (CPI)**

**Training needs to be completed within 30 days from the date of hire on a designated date provided by onboarding. Staff need to be certified at the commensurate level for their role to perform their job duties (staff will be taken off the schedule if certification is not achieved).

To perform this job you must be able to carry out all essential functions successfully. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable qualified individuals with disabilities to perform the job.
